    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03144.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <handShift rend="printed"/>
                <name type="place">HOTEL CHATHAM</name>
                    <name type="place">67 &amp; 69, RUE NEUVE ST AUGUSTIN</name>
                        <name type="place">PARIS</name>
     <!--               <date when="1874-11-06"/>-->
                </dateline>
                <handShift rend="manuscript"/>
                <salute>My dear Walt Whitman.</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>In London last week I met many mutual friends who were asking after you and wondering when you would 
                come over to the Great Smoky Capital&#8212;friends who know you only by your books. Last 
                winters stay of Rome, the author of 
                "Cleopatra" you remember, asked me for your photo, and I gave it him to contemplate and he has it 
                yet: Are you coming, and when? Most like I shall              
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03144.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>           
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.03144.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                return to the States this winter and then visit Washington for I have never yet seen our national 
                Capitol.</p>
            <p>The news of the great democratic virtues has first reached us and all Paris&#8212;that is all American 
                Paris&#8212;is <choice><sic>teribly</sic><corr>terribly</corr></choice> excited: Of course this suits 
                me, born democrat as I am, but I trust it will not at all disturb the future of 
                <choice><sic>the</sic><corr>thee</corr></choice> 
                my dear friend the "good gray poet." My address is the Langhorne Hotel, London. Drop me a line.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours <choice><sic>fittfuly</sic><corr>faithfully</corr></choice>,</salute>
                <signed>Joaquin Miller</signed>
            </closer>            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.03144.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>                       
        </body>
